Given the emphasis on mobile layouts being unforgiving, I would spend the hour improving the mobile responsiveness of one of the projects, such as The Checker. For example, I might adjust the CSS to ensure buttons and text display correctly on smaller screens by adding or refining media queries:

css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .personality-button {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 12px;
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .trait-display {
    font-size: 14px;
    padding: 8px;
  }
}

This snippet ensures buttons scale properly and text remains readable on mobile devices, addressing a common pain point highlighted in the text.
